  "text": "The cat's wounds were cleaned and debrided under general anesthesia (Figures 1 and 2) . A vacuum-assisted wound closure device was used to treat the inguinal wounds, as previously described, [CITATION_1] to assist with healing and skin apposition (Figure 3 ). The right lateral thigh wounds were debrided and treated with wet-to-dry bandaging. An esophagostomy tube was placed to facilitate administration of medications.",
